Community transmission has accelerated dramatically

With the development of the epidemic, the mode of transmission of the new coronavirus has shifted from overseas importation to community transmission and concentrated infection. Many countries have started to report confirmed cases of unknown transmission routes, and the number of confirmed cases has been increasing. South Korea is arguably one of the most representative countries in the world of accelerated community transmission.

Community transmission within South Korea was first noticed on February 17. On that day, a 60-year-old woman in Daegu city was diagnosed, making it the 31st confirmed case in South Korea. She is a member of the new heaven and Earth Church in Daegu city. Before the diagnosis, she visited the local new heaven and Earth Church on four occasions, two of which were followed by symptoms, with more than 1,000 people sharing the same space.

The next day, South Korea confirmed 12 new patients with pneumonia who had come into contact with patient 31. One of them was an employee of the Oriental Clinic, and the other 11 were members of the new heaven and Earth Church. More members of the new world church were later diagnosed, and the outbreak spread from the original city of Daegu to many parts of South Korea.

A tramp steamer. Who Pays for the spread

International cruise ships with multi-national passengers, which are different from the community transmission on the ground and cross-border transmission, have difficulty in landing and landing during the epidemic period, creating many uncertainties for the overseas transmission of the new coronavirus.

The close environment and population concentration of a cruise ship, coupled with the possible risk of infection from central air-conditioning and sewage pipes, make it difficult for others to escape a single confirmed case. In the process of disembarkation and evacuation, if the epidemic prevention measures are not in place, it is likely to cause imported infections in the country. Overseas passengers who are allowed to disembark typically return to their home countries on flights, which could lead to a larger global spread, given the presence of false negative nucleic acids.

The diamond Princess, a luxury cruise ship, sped to Port of Yokohama on February 3 after discovering a passenger had been diagnosed with the new coronavirus, only to be greeted by a 16-day quarantine at the port. During this period, the number of confirmed cases on the ship has become higher and higher, with more than 600 confirmed passengers getting off the ship for medical treatment.

As nations move to fight the disease, so do nations

In the early stage of the epidemic, some countries vacillated in their epidemic prevention measures due to the influence of national conditions, political ecology and social culture. But as the global epidemic enters a period of rapid expansion, no country is immune. At the moment, while there are no national pandemic response codes to be fully followed, there is a global consensus on a number of initiatives.
